news.title: Madras high court orders authorities to issue free house pattas to 500 SC families
news.para: Petitioner P Selvakumar belonging to the arunthathiyar community said that around 500 scheduled caste families live in deplorable conditions in Teppampatti village.

news.title: NGT orders Ludhiana civic body to remove construction raised on green belt area
news.para: The NGT directed the MC to work under the supervision of the district magistrate and representative of Punjab State Pollution Control Board and asked the MC commissioner to submit a compliance report with the registrar general of the Tribunal within two months.

news.title: Chennai development body plans to build co-working centres in three places
news.para: In Chennai, these centres started emerging in early 2000 and picked up in 2015. They offer cabins with three-seaters and above, fixed desks, flex desks, and meeting rooms for people to choose from.

news.title: Housing prices in NCR & MMR surge 49% in five years: Anarock
news.para: Average residential prices in NCR increased from Rs 4,565 per sq ft to Rs 6,800 per sq ft between H1 2019 and H1 2024 while in MMR, average residential prices appreciated from Rs 10,610 per sq ft in H1 2019 to Rs 15,650 per sq ft in H1 2024, according to Anarock data.

news.title: Fire NOC must for buildings higher than 15 metres to get electricity connection in Delhi
news.para: As per Regulation No 10(7) of the principal regulations, the discoms may disconnect the supply of electricity in case a direction or order for demolition of the premises is passed by a Court, or DDA or MCD or Competent Statutory Authority, said the notice.

news.title: SignatureGlobal (India) reports pre-sales of Rs 31.2 billion in Q1 FY25
news.para: SignatureGlobal (India)'s collections in Q1 FY25 grew by 102% to Rs 12.1 billion. Net debt reduced by 16% to Rs 9.8 billion at the end of Q1 FY25 in comparison to Rs 11.6 billion as at the end of FY24.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government amends hotel building byelaws to boost tourism
news.para: Calling the move a ‘reformative step’, the spokesperson said: According to the government order issued by the housing and urban planning department, the Building Construction and Development Byelaws, 2008, have been amended.

news.title: U.S. developer Panattoni says India should ease land acquisition process
news.para: While India offers opportunities for expansion, "the biggest challenge is land itself - permissions (and) availability of data to acquire land," said Robert Dobrzycki, CEO of Panattoni.

news.title: JICA signs pact for final tranche of Rs 4,657-crore loan for Mumbai metro line-3
news.para: Department of Economic Affairs (DEA) additional secretary Manisha Sinha and Ambassador of Japan to India Hiroshi Suzuki signed the loan agreement.

news.title: Telangana government mulls land conversion use to raise revenue
news.para: According to sources, there was a huge demand for such industrial land conversion for commercial or residential use. The govt too hopes to net close to Rs 10,000 crore from such conversion .

news.title: Maharashtra govt starts demolition drive against 800 illegal structures in Malang Gad
news.para: A forest department official, however, said that at present action has only been taken against illegal commercial shops built in the region and no houses were demolished.

news.title: Global capability centres drive office leasing in Jan-June 2024: Report
news.para: Bengaluru had the highest share of GCC leasing, at 39%, followed by Pune at 20%, while Hyderabad and Chennai at 17% and 11%, respectively, during Jan-Jun 2024.

news.title: Whiteland Corporation to invest Rs 5,600 crore to develop Westin Residences in Gurugram
news.para: The total investment for the project is estimated around Rs 5,600 crore, which includes construction cost Rs 5,000 crore while the land cost is Rs 600 crore. The topline of the project is pegged at Rs 15,000 crore.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government aims to complete eight lakh houses by March 2025
news.para: The minister reviewed the progress of housing units taken up under PM Awas Yojana scheme in different housing colonies in the state with the officials in the secretariat on Wednesday.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP issues notices to 38 builders, ask them to conduct surveys of societies
news.para: The order comes after plaster chunks fell off balconies of two residential societies — Paras Dews in Sector 106 and Signature Global Solera in Sector 107 — on Thursday.

news.title: House prices in UK fall by 0.2% in June 2024: Halifax
news.para: "This continued stability in house prices - rising by just +0.4% so far this year - reflects a market that remains subdued, though overall activity has been recovering," Amanda Bryden, head of mortgages at Halifax, said.

news.title: Foreign investors infuse $3.1 billion in Indian real estate in first half of 2024: JLL
news.para: In complete contrast, another property consultant Colliers India, earlier this week, reported a 6 per cent decline in total institutional investment in real estate at USD 3,523.6 million during the first half of 2024 as against USD 3,764.7 million in the year-ago period.

news.title: Two officials suspended for failing to stop illegal sand mining in Maharashtra’s Beed
news.para: The action against Purushottam Sudhakar Andhale (mandal adhikari) and Kiran Prabhakar Dandhe (talathi) came after senior officials found signs of rampant illegal sand mining near a river basin in Georai taluka, he said.
